    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-02T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-02T03:00:00-05:00" n="637"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d637">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3363: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-02T03:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 2, 1929—3 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>89. At midnight Ambassador Figueroa informed me that he had received a telegram
                    from his Government accepting President Leguia’s draft of paragraph 3 of article
                    number 1.</p>
                <p>They have now agreed on all questions and at 3 o’clock today, Thursday, both
                    countries will telegraph their respective Ambassadors in Washington the draft of
                    the agreement which will be handed to you for transmission to President
                    Hoover.</p>
                <p>Our translation of the full text follows, minus the preamble which was
                    transmitted in my telegram 85, April 27, 2 p.m.:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of memorandum. For translation as presented to President
                    Hoover by the Governments of Chile and Peru on May 14, see <ref target="#pg_798"
                        >page 798</ref>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
